<item>
            <title>[HBASE-14426] Authentication provider is hard coded as &quot;auth&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14426</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In ZKUtil.createACL(ZooKeeperWatcher zkw, String node, boolean isSecureZooKeeper),&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (superUser != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
        acls.add(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ACL(Perms.ALL, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Id(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;auth&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, superUser)));
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here scheme is presently hard coded as &quot;auth&quot;, actually it should be based on the auth provider configured at ZK. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
